76561198023059297,Recommended,426330,19776749,"Posted: 18 December, 2015",all,Clockwork Ninja,"First off, this is a text only choose-your-own-adventure, if anyone was unaware. If you value graphics over story or player decisions, this probably isn't the type of game for you.This is a pretty fantastic entry, which combines compelling storytelling with interesting mechanics and choice that seem to actually matter. I also enjoyed the game testing my own detective skills at a few points, challenging me to solve a mystery with the game only giving me helpful clues for correct choices instead of the direct answer like so many other games do, making it seem challenging without being unfair or obtuse. I felt genuinely immersed when playing this, which seems odd for a cyberpunk-fantasy choose-your-own-adventure, but it was just a very enjoyable experience that I felt a part of.My main criticism is that some of the decisions, especially the routine ones which you can adjust regularly throughout the game, should have to be confirmed before they are made permanent, as it is easy to make an error if you misclick or misread the option.I recommend this game to anyone who enjoys a good story or enjoys a game where the player's choices actually matter."
