,Recommended,426330,23880187,"Posted: 27 June, 2016",all,ArcaneM37,"This is a neat little choose your own adventure novel. Do not expect a game - this is an interactive book. No pictures, no sound, just reading. But if you know that that is what you are getting into, it can be quite satisfying for what it is.I takes about 6 hours to complete once (I took a nap with it on, so it says 9 hours). Though I have only played it once, the specificity of the ending and the huge variety of choices leads me to believe that there is a great replayability to this game. I love that it allows you to say one thing and mean another or say something and then when the time comes, make a different choice. That is very true to real life and I never felt like the game was making choices for me. I felt in control, and that is important in games like this. There was one plot hole that I found that ruined the immersion for meI chose to go back through the portal but could not close it behind me. Everyone cheered that I had defeated the Surgions even though I had actually left the portal wide open for them, but, overall it was an engaging experience, and I will definitely play again."
